result.execSummary:
Larry D Billups was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Larry D Billups was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Attorney Amanda Poznanski appeared in court earlier, defendant Larry D Billups not in court, in custody.  Amanda Korin Kirklewski appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Defendant has been turned over to the State of Mississippi. On motion of the state, Court orders case closed.

Defendant Larry D Billups in court with attorney Amanda Poznanski.  Defendant Larry D Billups in custody.  James C Griffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Defense received copy of Governor's Warrant.  Defense advises the Court that defendant does not wish to challenge the Governor's Warrant and does not intend to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court reviews Governor's Warrant.  Court finds that the defendant is the person wanted in the State of Mississippi. Defendant remanded to the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department pending extradition. Case adjourned for status conference, Branch 2. 

  Status conference scheduled for August 5, 2022 at 08:30 am.
